---
/**
 * Cascade test section. Pairs Tailwind utilities with element-level
 * "fake-Webflow" rules so we can confirm utilities win without `!important`.
 * Source for the extract-embeds + assemble-preview pipeline so the test page
 * round-trips through the same flow as real pages.
 */
---

<main class="p-10 max-w-3xl mx-auto">
  <h1 class="text-xl sm:text-2xl lg:text-6xl text-black font-bold">
    Tailwind h1 — should be black, bold, and resize at sm/lg breakpoints
  </h1>

  <p class="text-base text-neutral-700 mt-6">
    Paragraph. Tailwind <code>text-base</code> (16px) and
    <code>text-neutral-700</code> should beat the 24px purple Webflow-style rule.
  </p>

  <!--
    v4 spacing scale accepts multiples of 0.25 (so py-9.25 works, py-9.24
    does NOT compile). For non-0.25 multiples use bracket form: py-[9.24rem].
    Both shown side by side below.
  -->
  <input
    type="text"
    placeholder="py-9.25 (0.25 step) — should work"
    class="mt-6 px-4 py-9.25 border border-neutral-300 rounded-md w-full bg-white"
  />
  <input
    type="text"
    placeholder="py-[9.24rem] (bracket arbitrary) — should work"
    class="mt-3 px-4 py-[9.24rem] border border-neutral-300 rounded-md w-full bg-white"
  />

  <a href="#" class="block mt-3.5 text-blue-600 no-underline">
    Tailwind link — should be blue, no underline. mt-3.5 = v4 decimal spacing.
  </a>

  <img
    src="https://cdn.prod.website-files.com/6093bce33d9b4bae841b04e3/69dfcff6071b983201f5f097_logo-cleartax.svg"
    alt="logo"
    class="mt-6 w-[200px] opacity-100"
  />

  <hr class="my-10 border-neutral-300" />

  <p class="text-sm text-neutral-500">
    Pass criteria:
    h1 black + bold + responsive;
    paragraph 16px + neutral-700;
    input compact padding + neutral border;
    link blue + no underline;
    image 200px wide + fully opaque.
  </p>
</main>

<style is:global>
  /* fake-Webflow defaults: plain element selectors, unlayered.
     These compete against Tailwind utilities. Utility must win for the
     cascade strategy to be valid. */
  h1 { font-size: 14px; color: red; font-weight: 400; }
  p  { font-size: 24px; color: purple; }
  a  { color: orange; text-decoration: underline; }
  input { padding: 32px; border: 2px solid green; background: #ffe; }
  img { max-width: 50%; opacity: 0.3; }
</style>
